|{{sort|1999-03-25|March 25, 1999}}
|[[Metropolitan Remand and Reception Centre]]
|{{flag|Australia}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|John|Killick|nolink=1}}
|On March 25, 1999, librarian [[Lucy Dudko]] hired a helicopter under the pretence of checking out the upcoming [[2000 Summer Olympics|Olympic site in Sydney]].<ref name="Irish_Examiner">{{cite web|date = July 21, 2001|url = http://archives.tcm.ie/irishexaminer/2001/07/21/story8511.asp|title = Lucy in the sky with convict lands seven years in jail|publisher = [[Irish Examiner]]|accessdate = May 14, 2009|last = Ellen Connolly|quote = }}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Using a gun she forced pilot Tim Joyce to land on the [[Metropolitan Remand and Reception Centre]] grounds. Waiting was John Killick, who was serving 28 years for armed robberies. He jumped in the helicopter making an escape while being fired on by guards and cheered on by inmates. They landed in a park where Killick hijacked a taxi at gunpoint. The two were able to elude authorities for six weeks before being arrested at the Bass Hill Tourist Park.

Lucy Dudko, dubbed ''Red Lucy'' by the media, was sentenced to the maximum of 10 years and was sent to [[Mulawa Correctional Centre]] women's prison.  On May 9, 2006 she was released on parole after serving 7 years of her sentence.<ref name="metremand">{{cite news | date = May 9, 2006| url = http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/mastermind-of-helicopter-jailbreak-freed-early/2006/05/08/1146940478180.html | title =  Mastermind of helicopter jailbreak freed early | publisher = [[The Sydney Morning Herald]] | accessdate = May 28, 2009}}</ref> John Killick was released on January 22, 2015, but is not allowed to have contact with Dudko until he turns 80 years old.<ref name="killick_freed">{{cite news|date=January 22, 2015|url=http://www.news.com.au/national/john-killick-walks-free-from-prison-in-queensland-after-more-than-20-years-in-jail-following-helicopter-jail-break/story-fncynjr2-1227193428826|title=John Killick walks free from prison in Queensland after more than 20 years in jail following helicopter jail break|publisher=news.com.au|accessdate=January 27, 2015}}</ref>
